Preheat the oven to 180C/160C Fan/Gas 4.Spray 6 ramekins with non-stick spray.Divide the stuffing equally between the ramekins. Then crack an egg on top of the stuffing. Add 1 tablespoonful of milk or cream to each ramekin and season with salt and pepper.Place the ramekins in a deep baking tray and fill it partially with boiling water.Bake for 10-15 minutes until the eggs are set.Serve with leftover ham for brilliant Boxing Day breakfast.